-- Spain’s Montoro Rules Out Selling Loterias, Vanguardia Reports
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-01-12T07:31:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/spain-s-montoro-rules-out-selling-loterias-vanguardia-reports.html
Spanish Minister Budget Minister
Cristobal Montoro ruled out the privatization of state-owned
lottery operator Sociedad Estatal Loterias & Apuestas del Estado
SA,  La Vanguardia  reported, citing comments made by Montoro to
reporters at Parliament yesterday.  Montoro also said the government is studying different ways
to sell  Spain ’s state-owned airport operator Aena Aeropuertos
SA, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
